This Is A Major Pet Peeve Of Mine & I Felt The Need To Share With You All

Answering Emails Timely Is Essential For Your Business and Relationships …

Being able to respond quickly to your customers and colleagues helps you establish trust. When clients or customers know that they can reach out to you at any time and receive a response promptly, it makes them feel confident in doing business with you.

I know everyone is on their “self care kick” but taking 2-3 days to reply or simply not replying makes customers/ colleagues/ clients feel overlooked, under valued and it’s just rude!

You Never Know What Position Someone That You Ignored Will Be In One Day, Just Because You Don’t Need them Today Doesn’t Mean You Won’t Need Them Tomorrow 🫶🏾

One Of The Jobs I Don’t Play About!? Who Else Can Relate!? 
 
Our Baby Is Turning ONE & It All Just Happened So Fast😩 

I Think We All Can Agree That This Is Why We Work So Hard To Provide, To Give Them All Something We Didn’t Have Or Simply Give Them All That We Had Growing Up…

Here are three tips that our CEO @anthoniallen uses when scouting locations for client brand and creative shoots!

1. Know The Client’s Vision & Goals For Use of Images:
Understand what your client wants to convey in the photos, aligning the location with their style and message.

2. Visit in Advance: ( Not Always Possible But If You Can)
Go to the location beforehand to assess lighting, angles, and logistics. Take test shots to visualize the setup. Know what props are needed and prepare in advance for a seamless shoot.

3. Check Permits:
 Ensure you have the necessary permits and logistics in place to avoid any hiccups on the shoot day.

Creating can be so draining but here are some quick tips to transform your daily life into endless content inspiration of (((value))) 

✨Storytelling: Share personal anecdotes and experiences that connect with your audience. People love relatable stories.

✨Document Daily Routines: Capture behind-the-scenes moments of your daily life, showing the real you.

✨Highlight Hobbies: Share your passions and hobbies, as they can make for captivating content.

✨Explore Creativity: Experiment with different creative mediums, like photography, video, or even writing.

✨Ask Questions: Engage with your audience by asking for their thoughts, opinions, and experiences.

✨Show Growth: Document your journey and progress, whether it’s personal development, fitness, or skills improvement.

✨Stay Authentic: Be yourself, Authenticity resonates with people.

✨Solve Problems: Offer solutions and tips that help your audience in their daily lives.

✨Be Consistent: Post regularly to keep your audience engaged and returning for more. PERIOD

✨Listen and Adapt: Pay attention to what your audience responds to and adjust your content strategy accordingly.

Remember, the key is to find the unique and relatable aspects of your everyday life and share them in an engaging way.

Loosing Toxic Clients/People From Your Life or Business is NEVER a loss👇🏽

I don’t think as business owners we talk about this aspect of the business enough. We glorify our work and relationships and never share the hidden secrets of toxic clients that create crazy work environments that enable you from performing or that just makes you hate your job all together. We always say “the customer is always right” and pride ourselves on going above and beyond for those that “pay our bills” and sometimes we end up suffering. 

I’m so happy that I am in a position in my business where I can walk away from clients, partnerships, and people that no longer serve me or that simply just makes things difficult because of their own personal dealings.

There are still many of us that deal with an unwavering amount of rude, disrespectful and disgusting clients to “secure the bag” or simply to be honorable to your business and we push through, but this is a reminder to NEVER compromise your beliefs, integrity, or values for the sake of toxic business relationships.

Allah will bless you with something bigger and greater. Tag a friend that needs to hear this message 🫶🏽✨✨

AM I THE ONLY ONE: It took forever for me to fully embrace  the NEW year // this NEW season, last year for the FIRST time I saw the world that we live in from a different view ((on socials)) seeing all the death, & really seeing the politics play out in front of my eyes just has me looking at life differently.

This life is temporary. ((Period)) but we hear this all the time but I felt this in 2023, with the passing of dear Uncle, my Grannie, Cousins and THIS WAR!!! I needed a minute to pause ya’ll! Like forreal!! For once my business didn’t come first these past few months have been all about prioritizing my happiness, my family, and the few very sacred friendships that I hold and cherish.

The past few years I never think about my personal vision for myself and my family, partly because I was afraid too, one year I WROTE EVERYTHING DOWN & IT ALL HAPPENED!! (That freaked me out!!)

Entering this new season I plan to write down and execute because life is really temporary and a test for our next eternal life. I plan to give this stage the BEST that I’ve got in love, with my time, personal relationships and most importantly raising good humans and leaving a legacy of change! 

Every brand I work with must be impactful, must be halal, must align with MY CORE. When I give my time it must support the truth and greatness. The content I consume must benefit me in some capacity (SORRY if I unfollowed you totally not personal but long gone are the days I’m consuming content that does not benefit my health, wealth, educate me or impact me)

This is the season of creating value and becoming GREAT!
